CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `market_segment_characteristic` (
    `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY NOT NULL,
    `derivationFormula` VARCHAR(255),
    `description` VARCHAR(255),
    `extensible` BOOLEAN,
    `ID` VARCHAR(255),
    `maxCardinality` INTEGER,
    `minCardinality` INTEGER,
    `name` VARCHAR(255),
    `unique` VARCHAR(255),
    `validFor` VARCHAR(255),
    `valueType` VARCHAR(255),
    `composite_market_segment_characteristic_id` INTEGER,
    `market_segment_id` INTEGER,
    `geographic_area_id` INTEGER,
    `demographic_characteristic_id` INTEGER,
    FOREIGN KEY (`composite_market_segment_characteristic_id`) REFERENCES composite_market_segment_characteristic(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (`market_segment_id`) REFERENCES market_segment(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (`geographic_area_id`) REFERENCES geographic_area(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (`demographic_characteristic_id`) REFERENCES demographic_characteristic(id)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci

tables.name: market_segment_characteristic_value

    `toValue` VARCHAR(255),
    `unitOfMeasure` VARCHAR(255),

    `value` VARCHAR(255),

    FOREIGN KEY (`market_segment_characteristic_id`) REFERENCES market_segment_characteristic(id)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci

    FOREIGN KEY (`product_specification_id`) REFERENCES product_specification(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (`contact_medium_id`) REFERENCES contact_medium(id),

    FOREIGN KEY (`media_id`) REFERENCES media(id)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci
